The paper deals with handwritten Chinese character recognition using deep learning methods, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of normalization and feature extraction techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adaptation techniques to improve recognition accuracy, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
